The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, expressed his admiration and gratitude for the efforts of the California Office of Emergency Services in responding to the wildfires in the state. He acknowledged the devastating impact of the fires, with 13 people losing their lives and thousands of homes and businesses destroyed. Pence offered condolences to the families affected and assured them that the government is providing assistance. President Trump has approved a major disaster declaration for California, allowing FEMA to provide additional resources and support. Pence also announced that legislation in the House of Representatives includes $576 million for wildfire suppression in California. The Vice President emphasized the government's commitment to working closely with Governor Brown and the state of California to support first responders and help affected families rebuild their communities.